1. To run fastapi 
python3 -m uvicorn main:app --reload

2. To run streamlit
python3 streamlit run webapp.py

3. To build docker images and push it to Docker Hub 
A. create Dockerfile in local
B. identify namespace in Dockerhub (iamsasha in mycase)
C. docker build -t iamsasha/wineqlty-frontend .
D. docker build -t iamsasha/wineqlty-backend .
E. docker login
F. docker push iamsasha/wineqlty-frontend
G. docker push iamsasha/wineqlty-backend
*********************************************************
4. Create Kubernetes clusters in GCP using cloud shell
gcloud container clusters create-auto ml-expts --location=us-central1
gcloud container clusters get-credentials ml-expts --location us-central1
****************************************************************
5. upload frontend and backend.yaml to github
git clone https://...data-expts
cd data-expts/MLOps
kubectl apply -f frontend.yaml backend.yaml

kubectl get pods -o wide
kubectl get svc

access backend webpage with - http://<<EXTERNAL_IP>>:8000
access frontend/webpage with - http://<<EXTERNAL_IP>>:8501

We have to update the url in webapp.py to kubernetes backend service url. Right now it points to localhost
kubectl exec wineqlty-frontend-6979c6846b-m8t92 -it  sh
sudo
apt-get update
apt-get install vim
vim webapp.py
update url to http://winequality-backend.default.svc.cluster.local:8000/wine
(http://<svc-name>.<namespace>.svc.cluster.local)















